race.comment: POLARIS MISSILE (8) missed the frame last time but had been racing well prior to that, winning a Grade 5 three back before a placing at Dapto the following run. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. FLYING SICARIO (2) jumped from the rails and recorded a big win scoring by 6 lengths at this track over 365m (20.92). Has definite claims. THREE HUNDRED (4) was a winner in quick time back then got further back last time but came home hard into second and beaten 6 lengths at Richmond (18.45). Bold showing expected. UNCLE WALTER (7) has strong claims after a top-three finish last time out.
